*

01:57.285 --> 02:01.855
* I KNOW WE'LL BE
JUST FINE *

02:01.889 --> 02:04.625
* WHEN WE LEARN TO LOVE

02:04.658 --> 02:06.860
* THE RIDE

02:09.797 --> 02:12.733
>> WE HAD A PRIEST
WHO USED TO GIVE US GUM BALLS

02:12.766 --> 02:15.169
IN THE CONFESSIONAL
AT ST. ANNE'S.

02:16.570 --> 02:18.206
WE'D BE IN THERE--

02:18.239 --> 02:20.441
"BLESS ME, FATHER, I CHEATED
ON MY FRENCH TEST."

02:20.474 --> 02:24.245
OR, "BLESS ME, FATHER, I DID
WHIPPITS WITH A HOT TOWNIE."

02:24.278 --> 02:26.247
I MEAN,
YOU COULDN'T PHONE IT IN,

02:26.280 --> 02:30.484
BUT IF YOU WERE REALLY PENITENT

02:30.518 --> 02:33.487
AND FATHER ROGER COULD FEEL
THE SORROW IN YOUR HEART,

02:33.521 --> 02:36.424
HE'D HIT YOU
WITH SOME HAIL MARYS

02:36.457 --> 02:40.261
AND PUT A LITTLE GUM BALL
IN THE SLOT.

02:40.294 --> 02:41.595
[scoffs]

02:47.335 --> 02:49.370
>> TELL ME THAT YOU KNOW
THAT WAS WRONG, RIGHT?

02:49.403 --> 02:51.672
OTHER WAYS
TO EXPRESS YOURSELF.

02:51.705 --> 02:53.907
>> DAD, PLEASE DON'T SEND ME
TO MILITARY SCHOOL.

02:53.941 --> 02:55.609
>> IT'S WORSE THAN THAT, PAL.

02:55.643 --> 02:56.877
YOU'RE GOING
TO REGULAR SCHOOL.

02:56.910 --> 02:59.680
>> [scoffs]
BUT WHAT IF I SEE HIM?

02:59.713 --> 03:00.981
>> GO GET DRESSED.

03:01.014 --> 03:02.783
>> THAT'S ABSURD.

03:02.816 --> 03:03.784
>> WHAT'S ABSURD?

03:03.817 --> 03:06.620
>> [sighs]
NOTHING.

03:06.654 --> 03:08.922
>> MARSHALL.

03:08.956 --> 03:10.991
>> IT'S OKAY
THAT HE'S MAD AT ME.

03:11.024 --> 03:13.461
TO TELL YOU THE TRUTH,

03:13.494 --> 03:16.630
I'M PRETTY MAD
AT ME RIGHT NOW TOO.

03:18.366 --> 03:19.400
>> [sighs]

03:32.813 --> 03:34.948
>> SHE SHOULD BE PUT AWAY.

03:34.982 --> 03:36.384
>> SHUT YOUR GOB.

03:36.417 --> 03:37.985
>> SERIOUSLY,
WHAT ARE WE DOING HERE?

03:38.018 --> 03:39.787
WE'RE JUST GONNA TREAT IT
LIKE A NORMAL TUESDAY

03:39.820 --> 03:41.689
AND ACT LIKE NOTHING
EVEN HAPPENED?

03:41.722 --> 03:43.624
>> NOBODY'S ACTING, MARSH,
ESPECIALLY NOT YOUR MOM.

03:43.657 --> 03:45.526
>> RIGHT,
BECAUSE SHE'S INSANE.

03:45.559 --> 03:48.396
I MEAN, WE'RE LIVING
SO FAR OFF THE MAP,

03:48.429 --> 03:50.464
IT'S LIKE EARLY JOHN WATERS
OR SOMETHING,

03:50.498 --> 03:51.765
BEFORE DIVINE
WAS EVEN ADORABLE.

03:51.799 --> 03:53.834
>> HE'S KIND OF RIGHT, DAD.

03:53.867 --> 03:56.370
DO WE NEED A PLAN
OR SOMETHING?

03:56.404 --> 03:58.572
I MEAN, MAYBE SHE SHOULD
AT LEAST BE BACK ON HER MEDS.

03:58.606 --> 04:01.642
>> I KNOW IT'S MESSED UP
RIGHT NOW, OKAY?

04:01.675 --> 04:03.644
BUT WE'RE NOT GONNA BAIL
ON HER LIKE DR. OCEAN

04:03.677 --> 04:06.380
AND ALL THOSE OTHER USELESS
FREAKING DOCTORS WE DEALT WITH.

04:06.414 --> 04:08.482
SHE MADE A COMMITMENT TO GET OFF
HER MEDS TILL SHE GETS BETTER,

04:08.516 --> 04:10.017
SO...

04:10.050 --> 04:11.852
>> IT DOESN'T SEEM
TO BE GETTING ANY BETTER, DAD.

04:11.885 --> 04:13.721
IN THE WORDS OF POLICE CHIEF
MARTIN BRODY,

04:13.754 --> 04:14.888
"WE NEED A BIGGER BOAT."

04:25.666 --> 04:28.969
>> SOMETIMES THE STRONGEST THING
YOU CAN DO IS ASK FOR HELP.

04:29.002 --> 04:31.972
[chuckles]

04:32.005 --> 04:36.577
WE NEED A BIGGER FREAKING BOAT.

04:38.812 --> 04:41.815
[soft music]

04:41.849 --> 04:45.018
*

04:45.052 --> 04:47.455
[telephone ringing]

05:02.803 --> 05:03.971
>> [sighs]

05:04.004 --> 05:06.507
>> YOUR, UH, HOSPITALIZATION
IN 1989.

05:06.540 --> 05:08.075
>> YEAH, I, UH, I DROVE

05:08.108 --> 05:09.710
INTO THE BACK
OF AN ICE CREAM TRUCK.

05:09.743 --> 05:11.412
WELL, BUCK DID.
>> MM-HMM.

05:11.445 --> 05:12.746
>> BUT THAT WAS

05:12.780 --> 05:14.782
BEFORE ANY AUTHENTICATED
DIAGNOSIS, CORRECT?

05:14.815 --> 05:17.385
>> MM-HMM, NONE OF THE DOCTORS
COULD FIGURE IT OUT.

05:17.418 --> 05:19.887
UNTIL THEY DID,
WE WERE JUST...

05:19.920 --> 05:23.524
DROWNING.

05:23.557 --> 05:25.459
>> WELL, DISASSOCIATION IS--

05:25.493 --> 05:26.960
LOOK, IT'S SO TOUGH.

05:26.994 --> 05:28.996
I WANT TO COMMEND YOU
FOR MAKING YOUR WAY HERE.

05:29.029 --> 05:30.998
>> YEAH, I KIND OF HAD TO.
[chuckles]

05:31.031 --> 05:33.734
WE'RE JUST LUCKY MY SISTER
WAS ABLE TO WATCH THE KIDS.

05:33.767 --> 05:35.769
SHE'S NOT GONNA BRING THAT NEW
GUY OVER AND SLEEP WITH HIM

05:35.803 --> 05:37.771
IN OUR BED, IS SHE?

05:37.805 --> 05:38.839
SORRY.

05:38.872 --> 05:40.674
>> MMM.

05:40.708 --> 05:43.043
>> SO WHAT CAN TARA EXPECT
FROM THIS?

05:43.076 --> 05:44.645
>> WELL, IT'S
PRETTY STRAIGHTFORWARD.

05:44.678 --> 05:45.979
LOOK, YOU--
YOU CAN'T GET BETTER

05:46.013 --> 05:47.648
UNTIL YOU KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU.

05:47.681 --> 05:50.083
MY PROGRAM PROVIDES
A TWO-WEEK PROTECTED ENVIRONMENT

05:50.117 --> 05:52.052
WHERE PATIENTS
CAN REALLY DIG IN.

05:52.085 --> 05:53.887
ONCE WE START BREAKING DOWN
THE WALLS

05:53.921 --> 05:55.689
BETWEEN YOU AND YOUR ALTERS,

05:55.723 --> 05:57.691
YOU'LL BE ABLE TO GET
OUT OF SURVIVAL MODE

05:57.725 --> 05:59.827
AND REALLY START TO LIVE.

05:59.860 --> 06:02.430
YOU'LL HAVE INDIVIDUAL THERAPY
WITH ME, PLUS GROUP THERAPY,

06:02.463 --> 06:03.831
LONG-TERM RECOVERY PLANNING,

06:03.864 --> 06:05.466
ALL SORTS OF GOOD STUFF
YOU'LL FIND HELPFUL.

06:05.499 --> 06:07.868
>> I KNOW I WILL.

06:07.901 --> 06:09.503
>> SOUNDS GOOD, HUH?

06:09.537 --> 06:11.439
>> AND FOR YOU TOO, MAX.

06:11.472 --> 06:13.574
>> PARDON?

06:13.607 --> 06:15.976
>> I'VE FOUND A 12-STEP MODEL
OF FAMILY INVOLVEMENT

06:16.009 --> 06:18.045
IS EFFECTIVE
FOR TRAUMA RECOVERY AS WELL.

06:21.515 --> 06:23.050
>> THAT WAS THE MOMENT
I DECIDED

06:23.083 --> 06:24.852
THAT IT'S GOD'S WILL
THAT MARTY'S A MULTI,

06:24.885 --> 06:27.655
SO I BETTER MAKE ME
SOME LEMONADE.

06:27.688 --> 06:30.190
AND IF I GET HIM A CD
FOR HIS BIRTHDAY,

06:30.223 --> 06:33.527
I'M PRETTY SURE AT LEAST ONE
OF THE ALTERS WILL LIKE IT.

06:33.561 --> 06:35.496
[applause]

06:35.529 --> 06:38.666
>> WHEN I STARTED DISASSOCIATING
AFTER IRAQ,

06:38.699 --> 06:41.068
I SERIOUSLY THOUGHT
THAT EVERYBODY WOKE UP

06:41.101 --> 06:43.671
IN STRANGE HOTEL ROOMS
WITH PEOPLE THEY NEVER MET.

06:43.704 --> 06:45.739
>> DON'T THEY?

06:45.773 --> 06:46.740
[laughter]

06:46.774 --> 06:48.175
>> SINCE I WAS A CHILD,

06:48.208 --> 06:49.710
I ALWAYS KNEW THERE WAS
SOMETHING BIZARRE GOING ON

06:49.743 --> 06:51.078
WITH MY MEMORY.

06:51.111 --> 06:54.114
>> AT LEAST YOU CAN REMEMBER
BEING A CHILD.

06:54.147 --> 06:58.719
>> I'M SO JEALOUS OF PEOPLE WHO
CAN REALLY ANSWER THE QUESTION--

06:58.752 --> 06:59.720
"HOW WAS YOUR DAY?"

06:59.753 --> 07:01.154
>> [laughs]

07:01.188 --> 07:03.724
>> YEAH, I USED TO TURN IT
BACK ON HIM REALLY FAST.

07:03.757 --> 07:05.993
I'D BE LIKE,
"GOOD, HONEY, HOW WAS YOURS?"

07:06.026 --> 07:08.796
>> I GOT REALLY GOOD
AT HIDING IT.

07:08.829 --> 07:11.832
MY TRAUMA HAPPENED
WHEN I WAS 16,

07:11.865 --> 07:14.167
SO I DIDN'T START SWITCHING
TILL AFTER THAT,

07:14.201 --> 07:17.505
BUT, UH, WHENEVER I WOULD COME
BACK FROM A TRANSITION,

07:17.538 --> 07:20.541
I KNEW EXACTLY
HOW TO COVER AND GET BY.

07:20.574 --> 07:23.577
>> YEAH, WE'LL DO ALMOST
ANYTHING TO APPEAR NORMAL.

07:23.611 --> 07:26.547
>> I DON'T REMEMBER WHAT
HAPPENED AT BOARDING SCHOOL,

07:26.580 --> 07:29.683
BUT, UH, I DO HAVE
VIVID MEMORIES

07:29.717 --> 07:32.553
OF A FEW WEEKS AFTERWARDS.

07:32.586 --> 07:34.555
IT WAS A MONTH
UNTIL SUMMER BREAK,

07:34.588 --> 07:35.923
AND I COULDN'T WAIT
TO GET OUT.

07:35.956 --> 07:38.258
I'M SUCH
A TOTAL SUMMER PERSON.

07:38.291 --> 07:39.727
[light laughter]

07:39.760 --> 07:42.129
AND I REMEMBER
I WORE MY BATHING SUIT

07:42.162 --> 07:44.064
UNDER MY CLOTHES EVERY DAY.

07:44.097 --> 07:45.599
>> [laughs]

07:45.633 --> 07:47.601
>> AND WHILE EVERYBODY
WAS GOING TO CLASS

07:47.635 --> 07:48.936
AND GOING ON
WITH THEIR LIVES,

07:48.969 --> 07:51.639
I JUST SAT IN MY DORM WINDOW

07:51.672 --> 07:54.808
WAITING FOR SUMMER TO COME.

07:54.842 --> 07:57.545
>> DID IT?

07:57.578 --> 08:00.848
>> THE NEXT THING
I REMEMBER...

08:00.881 --> 08:03.116
IS SNOW...

08:03.150 --> 08:05.085
EVERYWHERE.

08:07.721 --> 08:09.022
I WAS AT MY PARENTS',

08:09.056 --> 08:12.560
AND SIX MONTHS HAD GONE BY
IN AN INSTANT.

08:13.894 --> 08:15.696
AND IT WAS JUST...

08:18.065 --> 08:20.734
WHITE.

08:20.768 --> 08:23.804
>> WHAT'D YOU THINK
OF THE SNOW?

08:23.837 --> 08:26.740
>> IT WAS...

08:26.774 --> 08:29.509
I MEAN, NOT WHAT I EXPECTED.

08:31.812 --> 08:33.914
BUT IT WAS BEAUTIFUL.

08:39.587 --> 08:40.754
[chuckles]

08:56.637 --> 08:58.005
>> I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT TO SAY.

08:58.038 --> 09:00.173
I AM SO SORRY.

09:00.207 --> 09:01.875
>> IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.

09:01.909 --> 09:03.944
I MEAN, MY MOM'S
A TOTAL FREAK SHOW.

09:03.977 --> 09:05.746
SHE'S ACTUALLY

09:05.779 --> 09:08.882
AT A HOSPITAL
FOR THE CRIMINALLY INSANE NOW.

09:08.916 --> 09:11.685
>> SHE IS?

09:11.719 --> 09:13.887
WOW.

09:13.921 --> 09:15.188
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
THEY HAD HOSPITALS

09:15.222 --> 09:16.590
FOR THE CRIMINALLY INSANE
ANYMORE.

09:16.624 --> 09:18.892
>> T-THERE'S, LIKE, ONE.

09:18.926 --> 09:20.861
IT'S OUTSIDE OF CHICAGO.

09:20.894 --> 09:23.897
A-ANYWAY, MY AUNT'S STAYING
WITH US, WHICH I'M COOL WITH,

09:23.931 --> 09:25.265
SO...

09:25.298 --> 09:26.800
SO DO YOU WANT--

09:26.834 --> 09:29.837
>> I FEEL REALLY BAD
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED.

09:29.870 --> 09:32.339
I EVEN TALKED
TO MY DAD ABOUT IT.

09:32.372 --> 09:36.677
LISTEN, I THINK YOU'RE THE MOST
AWESOME KID IN THE SCHOOL.

09:36.710 --> 09:39.246
REMEMBER ME WHEN YOU WIN
YOUR OSCAR, OKAY?

09:41.181 --> 09:43.751
[bell ringing]

09:46.887 --> 09:51.024
>> [sighs] SO YOU REALLY THINK
YOU CAN GET HIM TO COME OUT?

09:51.058 --> 09:53.026
>> SOME PATIENTS
HAVE AN EASIER TIME

09:53.060 --> 09:54.995
USING HYPNOSIS
OR SODIUM PENTOTHAL,

09:55.028 --> 09:57.765
BUT YOU--YOU'VE BEEN
EXPERIENCING CO-CONSCIOUSNESS,

09:57.798 --> 10:00.901
WHICH INDICATES PERMEABILITY
WITHIN YOUR SYSTEM.

10:00.934 --> 10:03.904
>> I'VE NEVER EXPERIENCED
CO-CONSCIOUSNESS WITH GIMME.

10:03.937 --> 10:05.172
>> WELL, WHAT ABOUT THE TIME

10:05.205 --> 10:08.308
WHEN T HIT
ON YOUR SON'S FRIEND?

10:08.341 --> 10:11.044
>> I COULD SEE
EVERYTHING SHE WAS DOING.

10:11.078 --> 10:12.045
YOU KNOW,
I DON'T KNOW WHAT'S WORSE--

10:12.079 --> 10:13.413
NOT KNOWING WHAT YOU DO

10:13.446 --> 10:16.349
OR SEEING IT
AND NOT BEING ABLE TO STOP IT.

10:16.383 --> 10:18.318
>> LOOK,
YOU CAN DO THIS, TARA.

10:18.351 --> 10:21.855
ONCE WE CAN ACCESS THE TRAUMA
BY PROBING YOUR ALTERS--

10:21.889 --> 10:23.824
AND THE ODDS ARE HIGH THAT
AT LEAST ONE OF THEM KNOWS--

10:23.857 --> 10:26.093
THEN EVEN
IF IT'S HARD TO WATCH,

10:26.126 --> 10:27.895
YOU'LL FINALLY KNOW.

10:30.430 --> 10:32.399
OKAY, LET'S HIT IT.

10:32.432 --> 10:33.801
>> OKAY.

10:37.170 --> 10:38.706
[camera beeps]

10:38.739 --> 10:39.840
>> [clears throat]

10:39.873 --> 10:41.742
[sniffs]

10:41.775 --> 10:44.044
>> SO MR. STUART
CALLED YOU HOT,

10:44.077 --> 10:46.847
SAID YOUR HAIR WAS
TOO PROVOCATIVE FOR DAYTIME.

10:46.880 --> 10:48.916
>> RIGHT.

10:48.949 --> 10:52.786
>> DID MR. STUART EVER MAKE
ANY REQUESTS FOR DATES?

10:52.820 --> 10:54.321
>> ALL THE TIME.

10:54.354 --> 10:56.323
HE ALWAYS WANTED ME TO GO
TO BROOKSTONE

10:56.356 --> 10:58.291
TO CHECK OUT
THE MASSAGE CHAIRS.

10:58.325 --> 10:59.760
>> THAT'S NOT A DATE.

10:59.793 --> 11:01.962
>> WHAT?

11:01.995 --> 11:03.931
>> IT WOULDN'T HOLD UP.

11:03.964 --> 11:06.800
LOOK, MISS GREGSON, IF YOU'RE
CLAIMING SEXUAL MISCONDUCT,

11:06.834 --> 11:10.203
IT HAS TO BE CRYSTAL CLEAR
THE ADVANCES WERE UNWELCOME.

11:10.237 --> 11:13.340
>> OF COURSE THEY WERE.

11:13.373 --> 11:14.808
>> [sighs]

11:14.842 --> 11:16.243
THE FOOD-SERVICE INDUSTRY

11:16.276 --> 11:18.979
IS A HOTBED
OF SEXUAL IMPROPRIETY.

11:19.012 --> 11:21.014
IT'S BASICALLY
INSTITUTIONALIZED.

11:21.048 --> 11:23.316
THAT'S WHY PEOPLE WORK
AT RESTAURANTS.

11:23.350 --> 11:26.019
IT'S NOT UNCOMMON
FOR YOUNG WAITRESSES

11:26.053 --> 11:29.289
TO DEVELOP FEELINGS
FOR THEIR MANAGER.

11:29.322 --> 11:31.024
IT'S OKAY IF YOU BOINKED HIM.

11:31.058 --> 11:32.059
DID YOU BOINK HIM?

11:32.092 --> 11:34.427
>> NO.

11:34.461 --> 11:36.196
I DIDN'T.

11:36.229 --> 11:38.999
[chuckles]
UM, MISS--MISS JACKSON,

11:39.032 --> 11:41.802
I GOT THIS JOB
TO GET SOME EXTRA MONEY,

11:41.835 --> 11:44.004
BECAUSE MY MOTHER
IS VERY, VERY SICK.

11:44.037 --> 11:46.506
I HAVE MUCH BETTER THINGS
TO DO THAN--

11:46.539 --> 11:49.810
THAN SPEND MY TIME
BEING IN A RELATIONSHIP

11:49.843 --> 11:53.113
WITH SOME LOSER GUY
FROM LOSER BARNABEEZ.

11:53.146 --> 11:54.181
NO OFFENSE.

11:54.214 --> 11:56.349
>> I'VE HEARD WORSE.

11:58.485 --> 11:59.853
>> SHOOT.

11:59.887 --> 12:00.988
SHOOT!

12:01.021 --> 12:02.389
>> IT'S REALLY OKAY.

12:02.422 --> 12:04.758
>> IT'S NOT OKAY.
WHAT IS WRONG WITH ME?

12:04.792 --> 12:06.459
I WAS ABLE TO BE CO-CONSCIOUS
BEFORE I CAME HERE.

12:06.493 --> 12:08.128
>> YOU'VE BEEN THROUGH A LOT.

12:08.161 --> 12:09.429
>> IT'S BEEN FOUR DAYS.

12:09.462 --> 12:11.298
WHY ISN'T
THE HYPNOSIS WORKING?

12:11.331 --> 12:13.100
>> THERE ARE SOME PATIENTS
THAT DON'T RESPOND.

12:13.133 --> 12:14.968
>> HOW AM I SUPPOSED TO GET
TO THE TRUTH AND GET BETTER

12:15.002 --> 12:17.304
IF THE ALTERS WON'T COME OUT
AND TALK TO YOU?

12:17.337 --> 12:19.506
>> THIS IS A PROCESS.
THEY'RE NOT READY.

12:19.539 --> 12:23.010
TARA, AND TO BE FAIR TO THEM,
LOOK, THEY JUST--

12:23.043 --> 12:24.978
THEY JUST MET ME.

12:25.012 --> 12:27.314
>> WELL, I LIKE YOU.

12:27.347 --> 12:29.016
I TRUST YOU.

12:29.049 --> 12:31.819
GOD, IT'S SO FRUSTRATING.

12:31.852 --> 12:34.354
>> THESE ALTERS--THEY USE
TARA'S BODY AS THEY PLEASE,

12:34.387 --> 12:36.223
AND THEN WHEN TARA'S OUT,

12:36.256 --> 12:39.459
SHE SPENDS ALL HER TIME
IN A STATE OF GUILTY OVERDRIVE.

12:39.492 --> 12:41.161
>> I'M SORRY.

12:41.194 --> 12:44.064
UH, BUT YOU KEEP SAYING,
"TARA THIS," AND, "TARA THAT."

12:44.097 --> 12:46.566
AREN'T WE SUPPOSED TO KEEP OUR
SHARING FOCUSED ON OURSELVES?

12:46.599 --> 12:49.002
>> THAT'S RIGHT.
>> YEAH.

12:49.036 --> 12:53.106
LIKE WHAT'S REALLY GOING ON
DEEP DOWN INSIDE OF YOU.

12:53.140 --> 12:54.407
>> I DON'T KNOW
HOW THAT COULD HELP.

12:56.944 --> 12:58.545
>> SO HOW ARE YOU DOING
WITH YOUR GROUP STUFF?

12:58.578 --> 13:00.280
>> IT'S FANTASTIC.

13:00.313 --> 13:01.849
I'M LEARNING A LOT
ABOUT MYSELF.

13:01.882 --> 13:03.316
>> [laughs]

13:03.350 --> 13:07.554
>> OH, IT'S JUST A LOT
OF USELESS YAMMERING.

13:07.587 --> 13:09.122
I THOUGHT I WAS GONNA ENJOY
MEETING PEOPLE

13:09.156 --> 13:11.024
IN MY SITUATION, BUT...

13:11.058 --> 13:12.592
>> YEAH, WELL,
IF IT MAKES YOU FEEL ANY BETTER,

13:12.625 --> 13:14.862
I'M NOT HAVING MUCH LUCK
BRINGING ANY OF MY ALTERS OUT.

13:14.895 --> 13:17.130
>> I THOUGHT THIS GUY
WAS THE MAN.

13:17.164 --> 13:19.099
AND AT HOME,
WE CAN'T GET THEM TO STAY IN.

13:19.132 --> 13:21.001
>> HEY, IT'S THE DUDE
FROM THE PICTURE

13:21.034 --> 13:22.135
YOU KEEP BY YOUR BED.

13:22.169 --> 13:23.937
>> IS THAT JENNY?
HEY.

13:23.971 --> 13:25.138
>> [whispering]
JENNY'S INTEGRATED.

13:25.172 --> 13:27.007
>> [whispering]
WHY ARE YOU WHISPERING?

13:27.040 --> 13:29.910
>> YOU KNOW HOW SOME PEOPLE
AREN'T HAPPY FOR YOU

13:29.943 --> 13:31.344
WHEN YOU'VE LOST
A BUNCH OF WEIGHT?

13:31.378 --> 13:33.446
>> OH.

13:33.480 --> 13:36.283
THAT--THAT'S AMAZING.
HOW'D YOU DO THAT?

13:36.316 --> 13:38.318
>> WELL...

13:38.351 --> 13:41.221
A LOT OF TIME AND HARD WORK,

13:41.254 --> 13:43.290
LIKE WHAT TARA'S DOING.

13:43.323 --> 13:44.457
>> BUT IT'S DOABLE, RIGHT?

13:44.491 --> 13:46.359
I MEAN, WE CAN FIX THIS.
>> MM-HMM.

13:46.393 --> 13:48.228
>> IT'S NOT LIKE TAKING ME
TO THE DRY-CLEANER'S, MAX.

13:48.261 --> 13:49.229
>> I KNOW.

13:49.262 --> 13:51.131
I KNOW IT'S A PROCESS.

13:51.164 --> 13:53.133
AND DR. HOLDEN SAID
IT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN OVERNIGHT.

13:53.166 --> 13:54.234
I GET IT.

13:54.267 --> 13:55.402
>> JUST AS LONG AS IT HAPPENS

13:55.435 --> 13:57.938
BEFORE OUR INSURANCE RUNS OUT.

13:59.672 --> 14:01.008
>> MORNING, FAKE MOM.

14:01.041 --> 14:02.275
>> "MORNSEYS."

14:02.309 --> 14:04.277
>> IS FAKE DAD STILL HERE?

14:04.311 --> 14:06.313
>> NO.

14:06.346 --> 14:08.415
[dryer buzzing]

14:08.448 --> 14:09.883
GUESS WHAT I DID.

14:09.917 --> 14:12.352
I DIDN'T SLEEP WITH HIM.

14:12.385 --> 14:14.521
I DIDN'T LET HIM SLEEP OVER

14:14.554 --> 14:16.056
AND...

14:16.089 --> 14:18.191
PERHAPS EXTENDED
THIS LOVELY THING

14:18.225 --> 14:19.226
YET ANOTHER DAY

14:19.259 --> 14:22.462
BY CONTINUING TO TREAT MYSELF

14:22.495 --> 14:25.065
LIKE A SPECIAL PRIZE
HE HAS TO WIN.

14:25.098 --> 14:27.100
>> OH, REALLY?

14:27.134 --> 14:29.069
SO WAS IT YOU

14:29.102 --> 14:31.238
OR THAT SPECIAL PRIZE

14:31.271 --> 14:33.106
THAT WAS HAVING
A SCREAMING ORGASM

14:33.140 --> 14:34.641
AT 1:30 IN THE MORNING?

14:34.674 --> 14:36.376
>> YOU'RE IMAGINING THINGS.

14:36.409 --> 14:38.645
HE WAS LONG GONE BY THEN.

14:38.678 --> 14:40.613
>> OH, REALLY?

14:40.647 --> 14:42.149
>> [laughing]
WELL...

14:42.182 --> 14:44.117
I DIDN'T LET HIM SLEEP OVER.

14:44.151 --> 14:45.318
>> OH, MY GOD!

14:45.352 --> 14:47.187
[telephone ringing]

14:47.220 --> 14:49.990
[humming]

14:50.023 --> 14:52.025
>> I'M A SLUT.

14:52.059 --> 14:53.326
HELLO?

14:53.360 --> 14:55.362
>> HEY, IT'S MAX.
>> HEY, MAX.

15:00.467 --> 15:02.402
>> MORE XANAX, MOOSH?

15:02.435 --> 15:05.272
WHAT IS THIS,
ANNA NICOLE SMITH TIME?

15:05.305 --> 15:07.207
SORRY, BUT EVEN IN FAKE LAND,

15:07.240 --> 15:09.109
THIS IS REALLY DONE.

15:09.142 --> 15:11.211
>> IT JUST
MAKES EVERYTHING BETTER.

15:11.244 --> 15:13.346
>> YEAH, BUT IF YOU TAKE A PILL
TO MAKE EVERYTHING BETTER,

15:13.380 --> 15:15.248
THEN YOU NEVER KNOW
WHEN THINGS ARE FOULED UP.

15:15.282 --> 15:16.616
AND IF YOU DON'T KNOW WHEN
THINGS ARE FOULED UP,

15:16.649 --> 15:18.118
YOU CAN'T FIX IT YOURSELF.

15:18.151 --> 15:19.519
>> BELIEVE ME,
I KNOW WHAT'S FOULED UP.

15:19.552 --> 15:22.689
>> DO YOU EVEN GET
WHAT MOM'S ALTERS DO?

15:22.722 --> 15:24.424
>> RUIN MY FREAKIN' LIFE?

15:24.457 --> 15:25.425
>> NO.

15:25.458 --> 15:27.594
THEY DO STUFF FOR MOM.

15:27.627 --> 15:29.429
SHE WAS PROTECTING YOU.

15:29.462 --> 15:32.599
JASON IS NOTHING
BUT A BI-CURIOUS CHURCH MONKEY

15:32.632 --> 15:34.467
WHO'S USING YOU
TO FIND SOME EDGE.

15:34.501 --> 15:37.070
>> THAT'S NOT TRUE.

15:37.104 --> 15:39.739
>> OKAY, SO MAYBE
HE WILL DO SOME GUYS,

15:39.772 --> 15:41.474
AND MAYBE YOU CAN GET HIM
TO DO YOU.

15:41.508 --> 15:44.377
BUT HE'S GONNA MARRY A GIRL,

15:44.411 --> 15:47.280
AND HE'S NEVER GONNA LOVE YOU
THE SAME WAY THAT YOU LOVE HIM.

15:47.314 --> 15:51.284
SO T CAME OUT
TO TRY AND PUT A STOP TO IT.

15:51.318 --> 15:53.120
>> YOU SLEPT IN THE TRUCK?

15:53.153 --> 15:55.422
>> YEAH, TOO MANY SIGNIFICANT
OTHERS AT THE RAMADA BAR.

15:55.455 --> 15:58.992
THEY JUST WANT TO TALK
AND SHARE AND STUFF.

15:59.026 --> 16:01.394
>> WELL, WHY AREN'T YOU SHARING
AND STUFF?

16:01.428 --> 16:04.597
>> WHY WOULD I WANT TO DO THAT?
WHO WANTS TO HEAR MY STUFF?

16:04.631 --> 16:07.067
>> YOU KNOW WHAT I THINK?

16:07.100 --> 16:09.336
I THINK YOU DON'T WANT TO HEAR
YOUR STUFF,

16:09.369 --> 16:12.172
BECAUSE YOU GOT A LOT OF IT,

16:12.205 --> 16:15.108
AND YOU'RE AFRAID
YOU MIGHT LOSE IT,

16:15.142 --> 16:16.509
AND YOUR VOICE
WILL GET ALL HIGH,

16:16.543 --> 16:18.111
AND YOU'LL SOUND LIKE A WOMAN.
[chuckles]

16:18.145 --> 16:20.347
>> YEAH, RIGHT.
SHUT UP.

16:20.380 --> 16:22.315
HOW ARE THE KIDS?

16:22.349 --> 16:24.517
>> THEY'RE DOING SO GREAT,

16:24.551 --> 16:28.021
I THINK YOU GUYS SHOULD STAY
ANOTHER WEEK OR SOMETHING.

16:28.055 --> 16:29.422
>> YEAH, RIGHT.

16:29.456 --> 16:30.490
>> GOOD LUCK.

16:30.523 --> 16:32.359
>> THANKS.
[phone beeps]

16:32.392 --> 16:35.462
>> WE'RE BEGINNING TO INJECT
THE MEDICINE INTO YOUR I.V.

16:35.495 --> 16:38.798
YOU'LL NOTICE YOU'RE BEGINNING
TO FEEL A LITTLE MORE RELAXED.

16:38.831 --> 16:42.602
OKAY, SO I CAN TELL
THE MEDICINE IS REACHING YOU,

16:42.635 --> 16:45.572
I'D LIKE YOU TO COUNT BACKWARDS
FROM 100 FOR ME.

16:47.507 --> 16:49.042
>> NOW?

16:49.076 --> 16:51.678
>> YEAH, GO AHEAD.

16:51.711 --> 16:54.447
>> 100...

16:54.481 --> 16:58.051
99...

16:58.085 --> 17:01.454
98...

17:01.488 --> 17:04.824
[slurring]
97...

17:04.857 --> 17:06.759
96...

17:06.793 --> 17:08.561
>> VERY GOOD.

17:08.595 --> 17:11.664
I'M WONDERING IF ANYBODY

17:11.698 --> 17:14.601
INSIDE TARA HAS A MEMORY

17:14.634 --> 17:17.170
OF A NIGHT
WHEN SOMETHING HAPPENED

17:17.204 --> 17:19.639
WITH TARA
AND A BOY NAMED TRIP.

17:19.672 --> 17:23.310
>> [breathing deeply]

17:23.343 --> 17:26.413
>> CAN ANYONE HELP US
WITH A MEMORY?

17:26.446 --> 17:29.216
>> WHAT'S IN IT FOR ME?

17:29.249 --> 17:30.450
[rock music]

17:30.483 --> 17:31.851
[cheering]

17:31.884 --> 17:34.287
DON'T MESS WITH BUCK!
[laughs]

17:34.321 --> 17:36.189
>> SO, LISTEN, BUCK,

17:36.223 --> 17:38.325
I UNDERSTAND YOU DON'T WANT
TO HAVE THERAPY IN MY OFFICE.

17:38.358 --> 17:39.759
>> OH, YEAH,
I'M DONE WITH THAT.

17:39.792 --> 17:41.328
>> GREAT, WELL,
THEN I'LL JUST--

17:41.361 --> 17:43.363
I'LL JUST HANG
WITH YOU, THEN, OKAY?

17:43.396 --> 17:46.799
>> YOU CAN HANG ALL YOU WANT,
BUT NOBODY WANTS TO TALK TO YOU.

17:46.833 --> 17:48.568
THAT'S WHY I'M HERE.

17:48.601 --> 17:49.702
OH-OH!
YOU SEE THAT?

17:49.736 --> 17:51.404
LICK IT AND STICK IT.

17:51.438 --> 17:53.406
>> YEAH, LUCKY SHOT.
WHATEVER, GET OUT OF THE WAY.

17:53.440 --> 17:58.845
>> LUCKY, HUH?
COCKY SUMBITCH.

17:58.878 --> 18:01.448
>> OOH!
[laughter]

18:01.481 --> 18:04.517
>> I APOLOGIZE
ABOUT MY FOUL TONGUE.

18:04.551 --> 18:07.687
I'M GONNA MAKE YOU
MY SPECIAL LADY.

18:15.828 --> 18:18.598
>> [clears throat] IF EVERYBODY
COULD JUST SIGN THIS CARD

18:18.631 --> 18:20.733
FOR TONYA,
THAT WOULD BE GREAT.

18:20.767 --> 18:22.335
AND WHEN SHE COMES BACK,

18:22.369 --> 18:25.472
NO COMMENTS
ABOUT MISSING EYEBROWS.

18:25.505 --> 18:27.374
AND YES, IN CASE ANYONE
IS WONDERING,

18:27.407 --> 18:28.741
WE WILL CONTINUE TO SERVE

18:28.775 --> 18:30.877
OUR SIGNATURE
VOLCANO CHOC-SPLOSION DRINK,

18:30.910 --> 18:33.913
JUST WITHOUT
THE "SPLOSION" FEATURE.

18:33.946 --> 18:35.482
YOU GUYS GOT ME?

18:35.515 --> 18:36.516
>> YEAH.

18:36.549 --> 18:37.750
>> UH, ONE MORE THING--

18:37.784 --> 18:40.753
IF ANYONE HAS ANYTHING
TO SAY TO ME...

18:42.655 --> 18:45.892
I ASK THAT THEY SAY IT
TO MY FACE.

18:45.925 --> 18:47.494
HAVE A GREAT SHIFT.

18:47.527 --> 18:50.630
>> THANK YOU.
>> ALL RIGHT.

18:50.663 --> 18:52.632
>> I'M GONNA SIGN IT NOW.

18:52.665 --> 18:53.800
>> THAT INCLUDES YOU.

18:53.833 --> 18:55.502
>> I DON'T HAVE ANYTHING
TO SAY.

18:55.535 --> 18:57.904
>> YOU CERTAINLY HAD SOMETHING
TO SAY TO CORPORATE.

18:57.937 --> 19:00.640
I HAVE FRIENDS
ALL OVER BARNABEEZ.

19:00.673 --> 19:02.509
THAT MEANS WHEN THERE'S
SOMETHING SQUIRRELLY

19:02.542 --> 19:04.344
SCOOTING UP THE FLAGPOLE,
I GET A CALL.

19:04.377 --> 19:05.645
>> I THINK YOU GET A CALL

19:05.678 --> 19:07.380
BECAUSE YOU CAN'T KEEP
YOUR PACKAGE

19:07.414 --> 19:09.216
OUT OF THE FACE OF EVERY GIRL
THAT WORKS FOR YOU.

19:09.249 --> 19:10.650
>> "PACKAGE" IS NOT
AN ACCEPTABLE WORD

19:10.683 --> 19:12.585
FOR THE WORKPLACE.

19:12.619 --> 19:14.354
YOU GOT THIS JOB

19:14.387 --> 19:17.590
BECAUSE YOU WANTED TO GET
OUT OF YOUR CRAZY-ASS HOUSE.

19:17.624 --> 19:19.392
YOU WERE LOOKING
FOR AFFECTION FROM ME.

19:19.426 --> 19:21.394
>> NO, I WAS NOT.
>> AND I WAS THERE FOR YOU.

19:21.428 --> 19:23.530
AND I STILL AM.
>> EW.

19:23.563 --> 19:26.433
CAN YOU JUST STOP ACTING LIKE
WHATEVER HAPPENED WAS IMPORTANT?

19:26.466 --> 19:27.800
>> IT WAS.

19:27.834 --> 19:30.670
KITTY, WE FELL IN LOVE--
>> OH, GOD, LOOK AT YOU!

19:30.703 --> 19:33.606
YOU CAN'T EVEN STOP SCAMMING
RIGHT NOW.

19:33.640 --> 19:35.942
>> HEY, CHUCKY!
IS THAT MY YOO-HOO?

19:35.975 --> 19:38.678
SO HELP ME,
IT BETTER BE ROOM TEMPERATURE.

19:38.711 --> 19:40.413
OH!
THIS STUFF IS FREEZING!

19:40.447 --> 19:42.282
THAT'S GONNA MESS
WITH MY SYSTEM.

19:42.315 --> 19:43.950
IDIOT.

19:43.983 --> 19:46.286
>> HOW'S SHE DOING?

19:46.319 --> 19:48.555
>> THIS KIND OF REGRESSION
TELLS ME I'M ON THE RIGHT TRACK.

19:48.588 --> 19:50.390
WHEN TARA FEELS STRONG ENOUGH
TO FACE THE TRUTH,

19:50.423 --> 19:51.391
SHE'LL COME BACK.

19:51.424 --> 19:53.260
WE JUST HAVE TO BE PATIENT.

19:53.293 --> 19:55.328
>> PATIENT--YEAH, RIGHT.
YOU'RE FREAKIN' $6,000 A WEEK.

19:55.362 --> 19:57.464
I CAN SEE THIS STUFF FOR FREE
IN MY LIVING ROOM.

19:57.497 --> 19:59.699
>> LISTEN,
I KNOW IT'S NOT EASY,

19:59.732 --> 20:01.701
BUT YOU CAME HERE
FOR A REASON.

20:01.734 --> 20:03.736
PLEASE TRY TO TRUST
THE PROGRAM, MAX.

20:03.770 --> 20:05.705
IF YOU NEED SOMETHING TO DO
WITH YOURSELF,

20:05.738 --> 20:08.408
I SUGGEST GOING
BACK TO YOUR GROUP.

20:08.441 --> 20:11.578
>> CHEATING ME, TAKING AWAY--

20:11.611 --> 20:12.579
>> [laughing]

20:12.612 --> 20:13.880
>> MORE WINE, CHAR?

20:13.913 --> 20:15.715
>> YES, PLEASE.

20:15.748 --> 20:18.518
>> I'LL TAKE A REFILL.

20:18.551 --> 20:20.887
[soft music]

20:20.920 --> 20:25.725
*

20:25.758 --> 20:27.260
>> IS THIS--

20:27.294 --> 20:28.861
IS THIS WHAT NORMAL PEOPLE
ARE LIKE?

20:28.895 --> 20:30.897
LIKE, IS THIS WHAT DINNER'S
SUPPOSED TO FEEL LIKE?

20:30.930 --> 20:32.732
[door closes]

20:32.765 --> 20:34.501
>> HEY, SWEETIE.

20:34.534 --> 20:36.903
NICK MADE
WHITE TRASH DESSERT.

20:36.936 --> 20:39.472
THERE'S PUDDING
AND MARSHMALLOWS

20:39.506 --> 20:43.610
AND BANANAS AND, UM...

20:43.643 --> 20:44.677
I DON'T KNOW.

20:44.711 --> 20:46.813
YIKES.

20:46.846 --> 20:48.348
[door opens, closes]
>> HEY, HEY.

20:48.381 --> 20:50.483
I BROUGHT JIFFY POP.

20:50.517 --> 20:51.784
WHO WANTS TO WATCH LOST?

20:54.387 --> 20:57.056
OKAY, I'LL GET STARTED
WITHOUT YOU GUYS.

20:57.089 --> 21:04.831
*

21:04.864 --> 21:07.367
>> YOU KNOW,
THEY SAY GOD NEVER GIVES YOU

21:07.400 --> 21:08.501
MORE THAN YOU CAN HANDLE,

21:08.535 --> 21:10.670
AND THAT'S JUST NOT TRUE.

21:12.872 --> 21:16.309
[crying]
MARTY'S NEVER GETTING BETTER,

21:16.343 --> 21:19.779
AND I CAN'T...

21:19.812 --> 21:22.749
EFFING HANDLE IT.

21:26.419 --> 21:28.921
[crying]

21:28.955 --> 21:30.690
>> DO YOU THINK
THAT NICK CAN TELL

21:30.723 --> 21:32.592
THAT I HAD A THING WITH NEIL?

21:32.625 --> 21:34.093
>> NO.

21:34.126 --> 21:35.828
>> BECAUSE I REALLY
DON'T WANT HIM TO REALIZE

21:35.862 --> 21:37.096
THAT HE'S DATING DOWN.

21:37.129 --> 21:39.098
>> HE'S NOT DATING DOWN.

21:39.131 --> 21:41.968
>> OKAY, WELL...

21:42.001 --> 21:44.437
I DON'T WANT HIM TO REALIZE
THAT I DATE DOWN,

21:44.471 --> 21:46.305
BECAUSE THAT WOULD LOWER
MY STOCK.

21:54.881 --> 21:55.915
[whispering]
DID HE HEAR ME?

21:55.948 --> 21:56.983
>> MMM.

21:57.016 --> 21:58.851
>> NO, HE DIDN'T HEAR ME.

21:58.885 --> 22:00.587
>> I THINK YOU STOPPED
BEFORE HE CAME IN.

22:00.620 --> 22:02.355
>> I DID, RIGHT?
OKAY.

22:02.389 --> 22:05.324
[people speaking indistinctly
on television]

22:14.501 --> 22:16.536
>> ...WHEN I SLIDE
MY HARLEY V-TWIN

22:16.569 --> 22:17.937
UNDER A PETERBILT

22:17.970 --> 22:21.040
AND POP OUT THE OTHER SIDE
WITHOUT A SCRATCH.

22:21.073 --> 22:23.142
>> THERE'S NO HIGHWAY 84.

22:23.175 --> 22:24.911
SHE'S QUOTING CONVOY

22:24.944 --> 22:28.014
AND TALKING ABOUT STUNTS SHE SAW
IN A BURT REYNOLDS MOVIE.

22:28.047 --> 22:30.383
WHAT THE HELL
ARE WE DOING HERE?

22:30.417 --> 22:32.018
>> ASK BUCK.

22:32.051 --> 22:33.119
>> I DON'T WANT TO ASK BUCK.

22:33.152 --> 22:34.554
I'M DONE TALKING TO BUCK.

22:34.587 --> 22:37.757
>> HEY, DOC, HELP ME OUT HERE.

22:37.790 --> 22:40.927
I'M TRYING LIKE HELL
TO COMMUNICATE.

22:40.960 --> 22:44.864
BUT THIS GUY--HE'S MAKING IT
REAL FREAKIN' HARD.

22:44.897 --> 22:47.133
>> YOU WANT TO KNOW
WHAT'S FREAKIN' HARD, TARA?

22:47.166 --> 22:48.868
WAKING UP IN THE MIDDLE
OF THE NIGHT

22:48.901 --> 22:51.137
NOT KNOWING WHERE YOU ARE.

22:51.170 --> 22:52.805
YEAH, THAT'S HARD.

22:52.839 --> 22:55.608
TRYING TO PIECE TOGETHER
SOME KIND OF NORMAL LIFE,

22:55.642 --> 22:57.744
BUT DOWN INSIDE
YOU'RE LOSING ALL HOPE

22:57.777 --> 22:59.612
THAT THE SUFFERING
IS EVER GONNA END.

22:59.646 --> 23:01.548
THIS IS NOT WHAT I HAD IN MIND
FOR MY LIFE.

23:01.581 --> 23:04.484
>> YOU CALLING ME OUT,
TOUGH GUY?

23:04.517 --> 23:05.752
>> NO.

23:05.785 --> 23:07.887
NOPE, NOPE,
I'M NOT DOING ANYTHING.

23:07.920 --> 23:09.756
I'M OUT OF HERE.
THIS IS WASTE OF TIME.

23:09.789 --> 23:11.023
[door opens]

23:11.057 --> 23:12.659
>> DON'T YOU WALK
AWAY FROM ME.

23:12.692 --> 23:17.163
YEAH, THAT'S RIGHT.
WALK AWAY, YOU WUSSY!

23:17.196 --> 23:19.532
>> HEY, BUCK, DO ME A FAVOR.

23:19.566 --> 23:20.833
IF YOU SEE TARA,
YOU TELL HER I'M THROUGH.

23:20.867 --> 23:22.168
I'M NOT DOING THIS ANYMORE.

23:22.201 --> 23:24.471
>> OH, I'LL GIVE HER
THE MESSAGE...

23:24.504 --> 23:25.638
ANIMAL!

23:33.212 --> 23:36.549
>> UH, HE SEEMED NICE.

23:36.583 --> 23:38.551
>> YEAH.
[both laugh uncomfortably]

23:38.585 --> 23:40.052
>> I THINK HE GOT
A LITTLE FREAKED OUT

23:40.086 --> 23:43.523
WHEN I TOLD HIM YOU LIKE
DOING IT IN THE SHOWER.

23:43.556 --> 23:44.591
>> NEIL--
>> CHAR--

23:44.624 --> 23:46.192
CHARMAINE, COME ON.
REALLY?

23:46.225 --> 23:50.530
I-I-I WOULD NEVER TELL HIM
ABOUT THE KNOCKING, ALL RIGHT?

23:51.964 --> 23:54.066
>> YOU--YOU HEARD ME.

23:54.100 --> 23:56.669
OH, MY GOD.

23:56.703 --> 23:58.204
NEIL.
>> YOU KNOW...

23:58.237 --> 24:00.573
>> LOOK, I'M SORRY.

24:00.607 --> 24:03.943
>> YOU--YOU HAVE BETTER BOOBS
NOW, ALL RIGHT?

24:03.976 --> 24:06.212
YOU CAN'T BE...

24:06.245 --> 24:08.047
WASTING YOUR TIME.

24:10.550 --> 24:13.620
AND, UH, BTW...

24:15.221 --> 24:17.590
I LOVED THAT BODY
THE WAY IT WAS.

24:17.624 --> 24:19.091
AND...

24:19.125 --> 24:21.828
AND BTW, BTW,

24:21.861 --> 24:24.230
THE THING BETWEEN US--

24:24.263 --> 24:26.699
IT'S NOT JUST KNOCKING,

24:26.733 --> 24:28.701
AND YOU KNOW IT.

24:28.735 --> 24:29.702
GOOD NIGHT.

24:34.006 --> 24:36.075
[engine turning]

24:36.108 --> 24:39.078
[woman speaking indistinctly
over PA]

24:39.111 --> 24:42.048
[indistinct chattering]

24:46.653 --> 24:47.987
>> TARA?

24:48.020 --> 24:49.722
>> HI.
>> YOU'RE BACK.

24:49.756 --> 24:51.724
I HEARD YOU WERE CLEARED
FOR TAKEOFF.

24:51.758 --> 24:54.627
[both laughing]

24:54.661 --> 24:56.996
OH, GOD.

24:57.029 --> 24:58.998
SEE IF IT STICKS.

24:59.031 --> 25:00.266
>> WHAT?

25:00.299 --> 25:02.268
>> OH, I'VE BEEN INTEGRATED
BEFORE,

25:02.301 --> 25:04.270
AND IT TURNS OUT
THAT SOME OF THE ALTERS

25:04.303 --> 25:05.838
WERE JUST HIDING, BUT, UM...

25:05.872 --> 25:09.108
I THINK THIS TIME
I'M GOOD, THOUGH.

25:09.141 --> 25:10.309
>> OF COURSE YOU ARE.

25:10.342 --> 25:12.679
>> [laughs]

25:12.712 --> 25:14.547
>> OH, WHO ARE THESE CUTIES?

25:14.581 --> 25:15.648
>> HMM?

25:15.682 --> 25:17.116
OH.

25:17.149 --> 25:18.785
UH...

25:18.818 --> 25:21.020
BELLA AND WENDY.

25:21.053 --> 25:22.121
>> HMM.

25:22.154 --> 25:25.625
>> THEY MUST BE
TEN AND 12 NOW.

25:25.658 --> 25:28.728
I HAVEN'T SEEN THEM
IN A WHILE.

25:28.761 --> 25:31.097
MY EX HAS FULL CUSTODY.

25:40.039 --> 25:41.841
>> HEY, CHUCKY.

25:43.776 --> 25:45.144
[sighs]

25:45.177 --> 25:48.114
>> CHUCKY,
THERE'S A 15-MINUTE LIMIT.

25:52.785 --> 25:54.654
>> CHUCKY!
>> OKAY, OKAY.

25:54.687 --> 25:57.724
>> I NEED THE PHONE!
HANG UP NOW, FOOL!

25:59.926 --> 26:01.127
I'M SORRY.

26:03.062 --> 26:05.998
[cell phone ringing]

26:11.037 --> 26:12.071
>> YEAH.

26:13.773 --> 26:17.009
>> I WANT TO FIND
TRIP JOHANNSEN.

26:17.043 --> 26:18.911
IF MY ALTERS WON'T TELL ME
WHAT HAPPENED,

26:18.945 --> 26:21.113
THEN I WANT
TO FIND HIM MYSELF.

26:21.147 --> 26:24.050
CAN YOU HELP ME?

26:24.083 --> 26:26.052
>> YOU GONNA CALL ME COWBOY,

26:26.085 --> 26:27.954
GET ALL MAD AT ME?

26:27.987 --> 26:31.924
>> NOT TONIGHT.
[laughs]

26:31.958 --> 26:35.361
>> I MISS YOU.

26:35.394 --> 26:38.965
[indie rock music]

26:38.998 --> 26:42.702
>> * YOU'VE BEEN KEEPING
SOMETHING FROM ME, BABY *

26:42.735 --> 26:44.136
* BY NOW, MAYBE...

26:44.170 --> 26:46.372
>> I MISS YOU TOO.

26:46.405 --> 26:50.142
>> * I'VE BEEN WAITING
FOR THE PERFECT MOMENT *

26:50.176 --> 26:51.978
* JUST YOU OWN IT

26:52.011 --> 26:57.383
* JUST TO SAY THAT I'M OKAY

26:57.416 --> 27:01.287
* WITHOUT A LOT

27:01.320 --> 27:04.757
* YOU AND ME

27:04.791 --> 27:09.128
* IS ALL I GOT

27:12.699 --> 27:15.902
* DREAMING

27:15.935 --> 27:19.872
* DREAM A LITTLE DREAM OF ME

27:19.906 --> 27:25.845
* SAY... *
